name: mahnooriftikharrr/Flood-Fill-Algorithm
description: Flood Fill  is an image-processing algorithm that colors all connected pixels of similar color starting from a given seed point, the same concept used in tools like the Paint Bucket in Photoshop or MS Paint.

name: mahnooriftikharrr/Stack-Based-Expression-Parser
description: This project implements a stack-based algorithm to evaluate infix arithmetic expressions. The program demonstrates the use of data structures, operator precedence, and algorithmic parsing to compute results from mathematical expressions mimicking how interpreters and compilers handle syntax evaluation.

name: mahnooriftikharrr/LinkedList-Labyrinth
description: A Java-based exploration project where I navigated and escaped a maze built entirely from linked memory structures. Each maze cell was a node connected by directional pointers (north, south, east, west).

name: mahnooriftikharrr/Arbitrary-Precision-Arithmetic

name: mahnooriftikharrr/SodukoSolver
description: A Java-based algorithmic project that demonstrates the power of recursion, backtracking, and constraint satisfaction to solve any valid 9x9 Sudoku puzzle.

name: mahnooriftikharrr/ShapeEngine
description: This project showcases object-oriented programming (OOP) principles through the design of a 2D game engine component that models, renders, and interacts with geometric shapes like rectangles and ellipses.

name: mahnooriftikharrr/Navigator
description: Navigator is a a Java console application that locates the nearest point of interest like a restaurant, park, or concert hall, based on user input for location and keywords. Think of it as a mini Google Maps built entirely in core Java using object-oriented programming and the Haversine distance formula.
